Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a #small pot{} over high heat.
Add half the @dried thyme{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later); cook, stirring frequently, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.
Stir in @Israeli couscous{2.5%oz}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and let sit, uncovered, until slightly cooled.

While couscous cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%oz} lengthwise.
Lay flat and thinly slice crosswise into shreds.
Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.
Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.
Peel @orange{1}, removing as much white pith as possible. Discard peel.
Dice orange into 1/2-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add Brussels sprouts and shallot; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until Brussels sprouts are bright green and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in half the garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.
Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

While Brussels sprouts cook, remove and discard any large stems from kale;
chop into bite-size pieces.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @kale{4%oz} and a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle}.
Using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead dough) until leaves are tender, ~{1%minute}.

Add Brussels sprouts and toss to combine.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in pan used for Brussels sprouts over medium-high heat.
Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, remaining garlic, and remaining thyme.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until panko is golden and garlic is fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Transfer to a plate.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @olive oil{3%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp};
taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use 6 TBSP olive oil and 1/2 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Add orange and couscous to bowl with veggies. Toss with as much dressing as you like.

Divide salad between shallow bowls. Top with @feta cheese{1/2%cup}(crumbled) and garlicky panko and serve.